data.description: Welcome to Dover Street, a recently renovated brick front home. This home features 3 bedrooms, 2 full bathrooms, an open floor plan, an abundance of natural light, and stylish finishes throughout. The first floor includes a spacious living and dining room, stunning kitchen, and a full bathroom with custom sliding barn style door. The living/dining room combination features a large front window, 2 new light fixtures, custom black accent walls, and stylish gray/brown flooring with beautiful staircase to match. The beautiful new kitchen has gray shaker style cabinets, butcher block counters, breakfast bar, blue penny tile backsplash from counter to ceiling, and custom raw edge wood shelving. Off the kitchen is a private patio area where you can enjoy a BBQ, test out your green thumb with gardening, or just relax in the sun/shade! Back inside on the second floor, you’ll find 3 bedrooms and another full bathroom. The front bedroom is the largest with enough space for a queen size bed, two end tables, and dressers. This room has a new stylish black ceiling fan to match the black accent wall and two closets with custom shelving and storage/decorative space above each closet. The middle bedroom also has great closet space and a new black ceiling fan. The rear bedroom also has a closet and would make a great office, nursery, craft room, etc. The hall bathroom has serious style and each remodeling decision was carefully made to maximize storage space and add convenience in what is usually a very awkward and tiny room. The basement is unfinished but has tile flooring, is freshly painted, and is great for additional storage… the sellers even left a built-in shelving rack for the new owners. The basement is also home to the laundry area with washer, dryer, and laundry sink included. This home has been given a cosmetic overhaul with gorgeous finishes inside and out and is totally move in ready. The first floor is cooled by a wall a/c unit and the 2nd floor includes a window unit in the front bedroom. Tucked away on a low traffic but extra wide side street and steps away from parks, playgrounds, shopping centers, and public transportation, the location is wonderful! Easy access to highways, hospitals, universities, and Center City. Enjoy restaurants, bakeries, and coffee shops in Grays Ferry, Point Breeze, Grad Hospital, and Rittenhouse… all just minutes from your front door! Don’t miss your opportunity to get into a great neighborhood at a great price. Check out this home today, you won’t be disappointed!
